<topic id="dita-ot-transformation">
  <title><?oxy_comment_start author="steven_higgs" timestamp="20150617T110306+0300" comment="Create a new topic (&quot;Creating a DITA OT Transformation&quot;) that will be in the &quot;DITA Authoring&quot; section and merge most of the content. The child topics can be deleted from this DITA map since they exist in the &quot;Transforming Documents&quot; section and they are linked here."?>DITA
    OT Transformation<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
  <!--Proofed-->
  <body>
    <p id="p1">To create a <uicontrol>DITA OT Transformation</uicontrol> scenario, use one of the
      following methods:<ul id="ul_ot1_lnt_1r">
        <li>Go to <menucascade>
            <uicontrol>Window</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Show View</uicontrol>
          </menucascade> and select <uicontrol><image href="../img/TransformConfig16.png"
              id="image_dth_1wv_sr"/>Transformation Scenarios</uicontrol> to display this view.
          Click the <uicontrol>New</uicontrol> button and select <uicontrol>DITA OT
            Transformation</uicontrol>.</li>
        <li>Use the <uicontrol><image href="../img/TransformConfig16.png" id="image_odd_1wv_sr"
            />Configure Transformation Scenario(s) (<shortcut
              conkeyref="reusable_oxygen_shortcuts_list/shortcut_ctrl_shift_c"
              product="author developer editor"/><shortcut
              conkeyref="reusable_oxygen_shortcuts_list/alt_shift_tc_shortcut"
              product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"/>)</uicontrol> action from the
            <uicontrol>Transformation</uicontrol> toolbar or the <menucascade
            product="author developer editor">
            <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol> Transformation</uicontrol>
          </menucascade><uicontrol product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
            >XML</uicontrol> menu. Then click the <uicontrol>New</uicontrol> button and select
            <uicontrol>DITA OT Transformation</uicontrol>.</li>
        <li>Use the <uicontrol><image href="../img/ApplyStyleSheet16.png" id="image_mw1_lnt_1r"
            />Apply Transformation Scenario(s) (<shortcut
              conkeyref="reusable_oxygen_shortcuts_list/ctrl-shift-t-shortcut"
              product="author developer editor"/><shortcut
              conkeyref="reusable_oxygen_shortcuts_list/alt_shift_tt_shortcut"
              product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"/>)</uicontrol> action from the
            <uicontrol>Transformation</uicontrol> toolbar or the <menucascade
            product="author developer editor">
            <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol> Transformation</uicontrol>
          </menucascade><uicontrol product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
            >XML</uicontrol> menu. Then click the <uicontrol>New</uicontrol> button and select
            <uicontrol>DITA OT Transformation</uicontrol>.<note id="note-001">If a scenario is
            already associated with the edited document, selecting <uicontrol><image
                href="../img/ApplyStyleSheet16.png" id="image_dx1_lnt_1r"/>Apply Transformation
              Scenario(s)</uicontrol> runs the associated scenario automatically. You can check
            whether transformation scenarios are associated with the edited document by hovering
            your cursor over the <uicontrol><image href="../img/ApplyStyleSheet16.png"
                id="image_by1_lnt_1r"/>Apply Transformation Scenario</uicontrol> button.
          </note></li>
      </ul></p>
    <p>All three methods open the <uicontrol>DITA Transformation Type</uicontrol> dialog box that
      presents the list of possible outputs. </p>
    <p>
      <fig product="author developer editor" id="fig_lvk_mzt_rp">
        <title>DITA Transformation Type Dialog Box</title>
        <image href="../img/sa_select_dita_transform_dialog.png" id="image_nwk_mzt_rp"/>
      </fig>
      <fig product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse" id="fig_amy_n4t_1r">
        <title>DITA Transformation Type Dialog Box</title>
        <image href="../img/ec_select_dita_transform_dialog.png" id="image_pny_n4t_1r"/>
      </fig>
    </p>
    <p>Select the desired type of output and click <uicontrol>OK</uicontrol>. This opens the
        <uicontrol>New Scenario</uicontrol> dialog box, which allows you to configure the options
      that control the transformation.</p>
    

    <p conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/name-storage-options"
      product="author developer editor"/>
    <p>The lower part of the dialog box contains the following tabs (only those that are appropriate
      for the chosen output type will be displayed):<ul>
        <li><xref href="dita-transformation-skins-tab.dita#dita-transformation-skins-tab"
              ><uicontrol> Skins</uicontrol></xref> (Available for <uicontrol>WebHelp</uicontrol>
          and <uicontrol>WebHelp with Feedback</uicontrol> output types).</li>
        <li><xref href="dita-pdf-select-processor.dita#dita-pdf-select-processor"><uicontrol>FO
              Processor</uicontrol></xref> (Available for PDF output types).</li>
        <li><xref href="dita-map-edit-parameters.dita#dita-map-edit-parameters"
              ><uicontrol>Parameters</uicontrol></xref></li>
        <li><xref href="dita-map-edit-filters.dita#dita-map-edit-filters"
              ><uicontrol>Filters</uicontrol></xref></li>
        <li><xref href="dita-map-edit-advanced.dita#dita-map-edit-advanced"
              ><uicontrol>Advanced</uicontrol></xref></li>
        <li><xref href="dita-map-edit-output.dita#dita-map-edit-output"
              ><uicontrol>Output</uicontrol></xref></li>
      </ul></p>
    <p product="author editor authorEclipse editorEclipse">For information about creating an
      entirely new DITA OT transformation, see <xref href="simple-dita-ot-plugin.dita"/> and <xref
        href="dita-ot-install-plugin.dita"/>.</p>
  </body>
